{
  "texts": [
    "We also assume that the phenotype and confounders are latent variables (Y and C) that we want to estimate and separate.",
    "The relationships in the causal graph are interpreted as follows: the arrow from T to Y indicates that treatments are applied to cells and are the main direct biological cause of phenotypic changes in cells in the perturbation experiment.",
    "The arrow from Y to O indicates that we partially observe the phenotypic outcome through images.",
    "This observation is assumed to be noisy and incomplete, requiring hundreds of cells and multiple replicates to increase the chances of measuring the real effect of treatments.",
    "In addition, the image acquisition process and the overall experiment are influenced by technical variation."
  ]
}